commit 8366b3d66884e0fe38d592af3ec8a5d44eff9afc
Author: Sayam Samal <sayam@zulip.com>
Date:   Sat Mar 21 04:10:06 2026 +0530

    decorated_channel_name: Fix icon-text spacing and alignment issues.

    The `decorated_channel_name.hbs` template had a space character which
    conflicted with the padding between the channel privacy icon and the
    channel name. This resulted in double spacing in some cases such as the
    modal title, where the decorated channel name was being used inline
    with prefixing text.

    This commit removes the extra space character from the template, and
    works on simplifying and unifying the spacing between the privacy icon
    and the channel name across the web UI.

    The `decorated_channel_name.hbs` template now contains an boolean
    parameter — `inline_with_text`. When set to TRUE, the decorated channel
    name is rendered as an inline component ensuring that it flows well
    with the surrounding text. Otherwise, it is rendered as a flex component
    for usage in components such as the dropdown lists and typeaheads.

    This commit also adds the relevant class to the channel privacy type
    icon to ensure that icon color updates successfully on live channel
    color change from the UI.

    Fixes #36987.

